content.description: Walmart projects its first quarterly profit decline in three years, leading Dow losses.
Trump administration aims to make cruise companies pay U.S. taxes.
Plans to dismantle a key science agency may negatively impact chip stocks.
Analysts question if Nvidia can beat earnings again amid Blackwell chip shortages.
Unemployment claims remain low despite federal worker layoffs under Trump.

outlook: Markets react to policy shifts, with retail, tech, and labor trends under close watch; Nvidia earnings and government changes may drive volatility.
